\par \fs20 \pard 
\par \fs16 \pard \ql \li600\ri0 \sb0 \fi0 n17 Daniel Griswold, \b0 \i \ul0 The Fiscal Import of Immigration Reform: The Real Story,\b0 \i0 \ul0  Cato Institute Center for Trade Policy Studies (May 21, 2007).
\par \fs20 \pard 
\par \fs16 \pard \ql \li600\ri0 \sb0 \fi0 n18 \b0 \i \ul0 See\b0 \i0 \ul0  Judith Gans, \b0 \i \ul0 Immigration in Arizona Fiscal and Economic Impacts Report of the Udall Center for Studies of Public Policy,\b0 \i0 \ul0  The University of Arizona (Jul. 2007) http://udallcenter.arizona.edu/immigration/publication/impactofimmigrants08.pdf (noting that economic output in Arizona would drop by $ 29 billion or 8.2% if all non-citizens, including unauthorized workers, were removed from the state).
\par \pard \ql \li600\ri0 \sb0 \fi0  
